A flight was forced to turn back because of a furious argument between a passenger and the crew over the price of a sandwich.

The Virgin flight had left Darwin, in northern Australia, for Perth today but trouble began when the man began shouting at flight attendants.

Passengers Kirsten and Claudia Lloyd told ABC News he eventually had to be handcuffed and taken to the back of the aircraft.

