'It kind of started over a sandwich, I think,' one said.

'Yeah, $10 for a sandwich, I think it was. Then he got all hyped up and started pushing all the flight attendants down the aisle.'

The sandwich at fault is believed to be a gourmet chicken and salad sandwich, created with celebrity chef Luke Mangan.

According to the Virgin in-flight menu it costs 10 Australian dollars - the equivalent of around £6.50.

‘He was rambling, his behaviour was erratic and he was shouting,’ one passenger told the Northern Territory News.

‘It wasn’t mayhem, but he disturbed a few of the kids on board.’ 

When the captain heard that the man 
was still causing trouble and continuing to complain 
it was decided to abort the flight and return to Darwin.

