Australian Federal Police, who are 
responsible for airport security, were waiting to arrest the man when 
flight DJ1432 touched down.

A spokesperson said he was taken to Royal Darwin Hospital due to concerns about his mental health.

A Virgin Australia spokesperson said the captain decided to return to Darwin because of the passenger's 'disruptive' behaviour.

She added that the plane would be ‘absorbed back into the flight schedule’ and 
passengers would arrive in Perth several hours late.

